[Horry County, South Carolina, is in the northeast corner of South Carolina adjoining Brunswick County in North Carolina. Logically the 2 counties have a common problem. See http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/united_states/south_carolina_90.jpg. The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map is at http://healthmap.org/r/7GE0.

It is unfortunate that horse owners will delay getting their horses vaccinated against this lethal disease. It always reminds me of one of our horse owners in the Florida parishes who, when told that his horse had died of EEE, replied that he supposed he had better get the other 5 horses vaccinated. Unfortunately a bit late when you have an arbovirus spread by mosquitoes. - Mod.MHJ]
